---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Hero from "@/components/Hero.astro";
import { COMPANY, FOUNDER } from "@/data/company";

const description =
  "Plainly Digital LLC is an AI-first consumer-apps studio. Every product is built around Claude as the reasoning layer, with security-first architecture and a privacy-by-design contract.";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description={description}>
  <Hero eyebrow="About" title="AI-first by foundation, not by feature." />

  <section>
    <div class="container readable about">
      <p>
        <strong>Plainly Digital LLC is an AI-first consumer-apps studio.</strong>
        Every product in the suite is built around Claude Sonnet 4.6 (Anthropic)
        as the reasoning layer &mdash; multi-turn coaching, document
        understanding, scam classification, transaction-aware insights, and
        personalized recommendations all depend on frontier language-model
        capabilities. Without that layer, the products would not exist. With it,
        they do things rule-based systems can't.
      </p>
      <p>
        See the <a href="/ai">AI architecture page</a> for the per-product
        model assignments and the specific tasks the AI performs in each app.
      </p>
      <p>
        The apps in this suite started as solutions to problems I had myself:
        a confusing benefits letter that took two hours to decode, a pet sitter
        who needed to know seventeen things and ended up missing four of them,
        finance content built for the people writing finance content, and so on.
        Plainly Digital is the small studio that turns those into AI-native
        mobile apps anyone can use &mdash; engineered with the security
        discipline of someone who builds compliance tools for a living
        (encrypted at rest, hardened at the API layer, AI-governed at the
        model layer).
      </p>

      <h2>The team</h2>
      <p>
        {COMPANY.shortName} is founded and built by <strong>{FOUNDER.name}</strong>,
        {FOUNDER.role}. {FOUNDER.name.split(" ").slice(-1)[0]} is a
        cybersecurity professional who has spent a career securing software and
        building compliance tooling, and started {COMPANY.shortName} to put
        that same discipline behind AI-native consumer apps — software built to
        make everyday life a little easier, and the world a little better.
      </p>
      <p>
        That background shows up in how every product is engineered: sensitive
        data encrypted at rest, APIs hardened and budget-capped, AI calls
        governed with input/output guardrails, crisis routing that's never
        gated, and NIST AI RMF&ndash;aligned audit logging. Security-first and
        AI-first are the same decision here.
      </p>
      {FOUNDER.linkedin && (
        <p>
          Connect on <a href={FOUNDER.linkedin} rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>.
        </p>
      )}

      <h2>How the business works</h2>
      <p>
        {COMPANY.legalName} is a {COMPANY.state}-registered consumer-software
        company, founded in {COMPANY.founded}. It's a digital-native business:
        subscription software, free to start with paid monthly and annual
        tiers. Patet, our AI money coach, is live at
        <a href="https://patet.plainlydigital.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">patet.plainlydigital.com</a>.
        Revenue scales with software and users &mdash; not consulting, not
        services, not per-project billing. Every product is built around
        Claude as the reasoning layer and runs on Google Cloud.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        One address: <a href="mailto:apps@plainlydigital.com"
          >apps@plainlydigital.com</a
        >. App support, business, security disclosures, partnerships &mdash;
        all the same inbox.
      </p>

      <h2>Security disclosure</h2>
      <p>
        If you find a security issue, please email
        <a href="mailto:apps@plainlydigital.com">apps@plainlydigital.com</a>.
        See <a href="/.well-known/security.txt"><code>/.well-known/security.txt</code></a>
        for our coordinated disclosure preferences.
      </p>

      <h2>Legal</h2>
      <p>
        Plainly Digital LLC is registered in Tennessee. Each app has its own
        privacy policy and terms of service:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Patet &mdash;
          <a href="/patet/privacy">privacy</a>,
          <a href="/patet/terms">terms</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          ClearDoc &mdash;
          <a href="/cleardoc/privacy">privacy</a>,
          <a href="/cleardoc/terms">terms</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          SitterSheet &mdash;
          <a href="/sittersheet/privacy">privacy</a>,
          <a href="/sittersheet/terms">terms</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          This site &mdash;
          <a href="/privacy">privacy</a>,
          <a href="/terms">terms</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about p,
  .about li {
    color: var(--pd-ink-soft);
  }
  .about h2 {
    margin-top: var(--pd-space-12);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }
</style>
